article.headline: Utah St. 80, Troy 39
article.story: LOGAN, Utah -- Brian Green scored 23 points and made six 3-pointers to lead Utah State to an 80-39 victory against Troy in the World Vision Invitational on Thursday night. Brockeith Pane and Tyler Newbold had 10 points each for the Aggies (11-2). Tai Wesley had 12 rebounds. Troy (2-11) shot just 19.7 percent from the field, managing only 12 field goals. Levan Patsatsia had nine points and Regis Huddleston eight for the Trojans. After leading by 27 points at halftime, Utah State built a 70-22 cushion after Green, Newbold and James Walker combined to make four consecutive 3-pointers. The game was the finale of the three-day, four-team World Vision Invitational.
